<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Demange" authorityYear="1971" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirostreptidae" genus="Lobogonus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lobogonus trilobatus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Lobogonus trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Demange, 1971, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation author="Demange, JM" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Institut Fondamental d'Afrique Noire" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="191 - 240" refId="B5" refString="Demange, JM, 1971. Le massif des Monts Loma (Sierra Leone), fascicule 1. VII. Myriapodes Diplopodes. Memoires de l'Institut Fondamental d'Afrique Noire 86: 191 - 240" title="Le massif des Monts Loma (Sierra Leone), fascicule 1. VII. Myriapodes Diplopodes." volume="86" year="1971">Demange 1971</bibRefCitation>
, with modifications). A genus of large millipedes (up to ca 200 mm long) with relatively long legs (80% of maximum body diameter). Gonocoxite stout and large, ending with a thick apicolateral projection (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lobogonus trilobatus Demange, 1971, ♂ syntype. A habitus, lateral view B transverse section of midbody segment C right gonopod, posterior view D left telopodite, anterior view E tip of telopodite. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, bs = basomere, lap = latero-apical process, map = meso-apical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, sb = seminal branch. Scale bars: 10 mm (A); 1 mm (C); 500 µm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404815" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">1C</figureCitation>
, lap); telopodite thick and short, distally characterized by three well-differentiated lobes and a thin seminal branch (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lobogonus trilobatus Demange, 1971, ♂ syntype. A habitus, lateral view B transverse section of midbody segment C right gonopod, posterior view D left telopodite, anterior view E tip of telopodite. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, bs = basomere, lap = latero-apical process, map = meso-apical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, sb = seminal branch. Scale bars: 10 mm (A); 1 mm (C); 500 µm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404815" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">1D, E</figureCitation>
, sb).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
